  <h2>Technical Information and Schedule</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>The day will start at 8:30am with breakfast and registration; talks will begin at 9:30am. It’s advisable that you arrive before 9:30am, so that we can set up your notebook for a test run and make sure everything works.</li>
    <li>As a speaker, you won’t have to queue at the venue for checking in, you can come to the registration desk directly. You’ll then get your speaker bag with your conference pass.</li>
    <li>Projector resolution is full HD (1080p), that is 1920x1080.</li>
    <li>You can connect to the projector with VGA, HDMI or DVI. Adapters will be provided.</li>
    <li>You can connect your notebook to the audio, cable will be provided.</li>
    <li>There will be power supplies.</li>
    <li>Please be prepared to provide the technicians with your presentation, e.g. via USB stick.</li>
    <li>You’ll be given a headset, so you’ll have your hands free during your talk.</li>
    <li>A presentation clicker can be provided.</li>
    <li>WiFi as well as ethernet access will be available. It should be reliable, but you’re always better off having a fallback option in case the connection doesn’t work.</li>
    <li>Each talk slot is 30 minutes, no Q&amp;A. We believe it’s way better to discuss things in smaller groups afterwards and you’ll have enough time and space to do that.</li>
    <li>All talks will be professionally recorded and released after the conference. They will be publicly accessible for free, so that everyone can learn from the awesome talks you delivered. If you wish not to have your talk recorded and published, or have any issues regarding copyright (incl. embedded images or similar), please let us know.</li>
    <li>If you plan to show any code, remember to increase the font size. A lot ;-)</li>
  </ul>


