  </p>

  <h2>Code of Conduct</h2>
  <p>One last but very important point: We’re an inclusive community event and we want CSSconf EU to be a safe place for everyone to make new friends, share knowledge, learn new stuff, get excited and gain insights reglardless of skin colour, gender, religious views, sexual preference, etc.</p>
  <p>We want our community to be tolerant and welcoming, and everyone at the conference is required to agree and act according to our <a href="http://2015.cssconf.eu/code-of-conduct" target="_blank">Code of Conduct</a>. – Should you encounter or observe any form of harrassment, please let us know and we’ll take care of it!</p>

